Ndubuisi Orji, Abuja The speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, on Thursday named former chief whip, Alhassan Ado-Doguwa, as the House leader. Gbajabiamila said members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in a communication sent to him also nominated Tahir Monguno as chief whip, while Peter Akpatason and Nkeiruka Onyejeocha were nominated to serve as deputy House leader and deputy chief whip respectively.